<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/inec-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1" alt="INEC to combine Kogi guber election with senatorial poll on Nov. 16" class="amp-wp-295b586"> Omeiza Ajayi, Abuja The Independent National Electoral Commission INEC has fixed November 16 for the conduct of a fresh election into the Kogi West Senatorial Constituency seat. The election is being conducted on the same day with the Governorship Election in the state. INEC National Commissioner and Chairman of its Information and Voter Education Committee, Barr. Festus Okoye announced this in a statement yesterday. According to him, the commission had met on Monday and considered the timetable and dates of elections for the Sabuwa State Constituency of Katsina State and Kogi West Senatorial District. Continue reading INEC to combine Kogi guber election with senatorial poll on Nov. 16 at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard